.SH MakeGrid2D
Create a 2D cylindrical map of arbitrary grid spacing from a set of
spherical harmonic coefficients.
.SH Usage
call MakeGrid2D (\f[CR]grid\f[R], \f[CR]cilm\f[R], \f[CR]lmax\f[R],
\f[CR]interval\f[R], \f[CR]nlat\f[R], \f[CR]nlong\f[R], \f[CR]norm\f[R],
\f[CR]csphase\f[R], \f[CR]f\f[R], \f[CR]a\f[R], \f[CR]north\f[R],
\f[CR]south\f[R], \f[CR]east\f[R], \f[CR]west\f[R], \f[CR]dealloc\f[R],
\f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
